genresAdvancedInfo.name: new england experimental
genresAdvancedInfo.description: New England experimental is a genre that pushes the boundaries of traditional music. It often incorporates unconventional sounds and instruments, such as field recordings and found objects, to create unique and experimental compositions that challenge the listener's expectations.
